---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
	title="Theming & dark mode"
	description="How Tideway themes: a semantic role layer over the palette, and dark mode with color-scheme and light-dark()."
	active="theming"
>
	<article class="doc">
		<p class="doc__eyebrow">Guide</p>
		<h1 class="doc__title">Theming &amp; dark mode</h1>
		<p class="doc__lead">
			Theming works because color is referenced through a semantic role layer, never the palette
			directly. Redefining that layer re-themes the whole project — dark mode, a rebrand — without
			touching a single component, and without the switch ever leaking into a selector.
		</p>

		<section class="doc__section">
			<h2 class="doc__section-title">Two tiers of tokens</h2>
			<div class="doc__list">
				<p class="doc__item">
					<strong>Primitives</strong> — the palette (<code class="doc__code">--color-blue-600</code>)
					and the other scales. A fixed vocabulary, never referenced for color inside a component.
				</p>
				<p class="doc__item">
					<strong>Semantic roles</strong> — named roles (<code class="doc__code">--surface</code>,
					<code class="doc__code">--text</code>, <code class="doc__code">--border</code>,
					<code class="doc__code">--accent</code>, …) that map to primitives. Components read color
					only from these.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="doc__section">
			<h2 class="doc__section-title">Dark mode</h2>
			<p class="doc__text">
				Use the browser-native pairing: <code class="doc__code">color-scheme</code> plus
				<code class="doc__code">light-dark()</code>. One declaration per role holds both themes, native
				controls (form fields, scrollbars) theme automatically, and the switch stays entirely in the
				token layer.
			</p>
			<div class="doc__list">
				<p class="doc__item">
					A plain light value precedes each <code class="doc__code">light-dark()</code> line as a
					fallback, so browsers without support stay on a working light theme.
				</p>
				<p class="doc__item">
					<code class="doc__code">&lt;meta name="color-scheme" content="light dark"&gt;</code> in the
					head paints the right background immediately and avoids a flash.
				</p>
				<p class="doc__item">
					Auto mode follows the OS with zero JavaScript. A toggle that remembers a manual choice needs
					only a few lines of JS to set <code class="doc__code">data-theme</code> — try the switch in
					this site's header.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>
	</article>
</DocsLayout>
